      "rationale": "NIH is the primary QoI and is directly compared against the clinical threshold of 0.005 g/100 L per ISO 10993-4 guidance. Mapping reviewed by a haematologist consultant. Gap at Gradation 5 arises because the mapping has not been validated against patient outcome data; reliance on in-vitro surrogate introduces residual uncertainty."
