      "rationale": "Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law is the most widely used hemolysis model in the literature but is known to over-predict NIH under high-shear intermittent exposure. No comparison against the Arora or Taskin mechanistic models was performed. Model-form sensitivity was not quantified. This is a significant gap at MRL 5."
